[SN]TITLE[SN]
Scottish Premiership: Saturday's reports & Sunday's previews

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Inverness Caledonian Thistle were relegated to the Scottish Championship on Saturday despite beating Motherwell in their final game, with Hamilton Academical thrashing Dundee to book a place in the Premiership play-off final.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
On Sunday champions Celtic look to complete the first-ever unbeaten 38-game campaign in Scotland's top flight.
Saturday reports
Hamilton Academical 4-0 Dundee
Inverness CT 3-2 Motherwell
Kilmarnock 1-2 Ross County
Sunday previews (12:30 kick-offs)
Celtic v Hearts
Partick Thistle v Aberdeen
St Johnstone v Rangers
